snippet.textDisplay:
Jenna, I have a secret to tell you, Cermet isn’t actually an Italian Greyhound. He just looks like one. He’s actually literally a cermet. To turn him to normal, give him a cermet formula. Take 2 cups of water, and put it in a bowl, and add in 1 quarter of a pint of milk, then crush small pieces of his favorite dog treats and chop small pieces of chicken in the mixture, then mix for 3 minutes and 30 seconds. If you want to make sure it is mixed well, mix it for 30 more seconds. Finally, take a bar of Irish Spring Soap, then put it on a glass with the mixture like restaurants do with slices of lemons and limes (optional). Then have Cermet drink it. He doesn’t have to drink all of it, just at least 1 sip. He should return to his original cermet species in 30 minutes.
The cermet species does have some downsides to the breed, so make sure if these behaviors of the cermet species is ok with you:
Behaviors:
Molting/shedding skin (the way spiders do)
Even worse cravings for Irish Spring and chicken
Eating feet more
More howling
More borks
May occasionally eat Marbles alive
Will be even more nasty.
If you have any more questions, let me know!
